input.command:
ghx run pr.reviews.submit --input - <<'EOF'
{
  "owner": "aryeko",
  "name": "ghx-bench-fixtures",
  "prNumber": 448,
  "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES",
  "body": "run_1772555729706\n\nThanks for the PR. I found several blocking issues that need to be fixed before merge:\n- `src/utils/helpers.ts` has a syntax error in the `fs` import (`improt`), which will fail parsing/build.\n- `divide(a, b)` ignores `b` and always divides by zero, producing incorrect runtime behavior (`Infinity`/`-Infinity`) instead of a real division result.\n- `waitForReady()` uses an unconditional busy-wait loop (`while (true)`), which can peg CPU and never return; this is unsafe for production code and can hang tests/processes.\n\nPlease address these and push an update. Happy to re-review once fixed.",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 2,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "Typo in the import keyword: `improt` should be `import`. As written, this file will not parse and TypeScript compilation will fail."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 8,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "`divide(a, b)` currently returns `a / 0`, which ignores the `b` argument and always performs division by zero. This is a correctness bug. It should divide by `b`, and ideally guard against `b === 0` with explicit error handling."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 12,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "This is an unbounded busy-wait loop (`while (true)`), which can lock execution and consume CPU indefinitely. Please replace this with a bounded/async wait mechanism (event, promise, timeout, or cancellation-aware polling) so the function can complete safely."
    }
  ]
}
EOF

